-- Wal-Mart Chief Administrative Officer Mars to Leave: WSJ
-- B y   V i n i c y   C h a n
-- 2013-02-28T06:57:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-28/wal-mart-chief-administrative-officer-mars-to-leave-wsj.html
Wal-Mart Stores Inc.’s (WMT)  Chief
Administrative Officer in the U.S., Tom Mars, will leave the
world’s largest retailer on March 13.  Mars handles real estate, financial services and labor
relations, according to the company’s  website . He was
responsible for the legal department and served as general
counsel from May 2002 to February 2009.  Wal-Mart’s Asia spokesman  Anthony Rose  confirmed the
departure without providing a reason and Mars couldn’t be
contacted outside regular business hours in the U.S. The Wall
Street Journal earlier reported that Mars was leaving.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vinicy Chan in Hong Kong at 
 vchan91@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
